Description: Skip driver / browser-binary bundling
 Upstream's `setup.py` overrides bdist_wheel via
 `PlaywrightBDistWheelCommand` which (a) curls a Node.js driver
 bundle from playwright.azureedge.net at build time and (b) packs
 platform-specific browser binaries into a per-arch wheel. Both
 conflict with our PPA build: we run offline (PIP_NO_INDEX=1) and we
 deliberately do not redistribute upstream's bundled Chromium / etc.
 binaries. Drop the cmdclass override so pybuild produces a vanilla
 pure-Python wheel; users install chromium/firefox via apt and
 Playwright drives whichever the system actually has.
Author: Avalan Packaging Team <avalan@avalan.ai>
Forwarded: not-needed
Last-Update: 2026-05-18

--- a/setup.py
+++ b/setup.py
@@ -203,5 +203,4 @@
 
 
 setup(
-    cmdclass={"bdist_wheel": PlaywrightBDistWheelCommand},
 )
